So, obvious questions include: What is the transfer operator? What are the
 eigenfunctions of the transfer operator? Recall, given a transition function
 
\begin_inset Formula $T$
\end_inset

, the transfer operator is defined as 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\left[\mathcal{L}_{T}f\right]\left(x\right)=etc
\]

\end_inset

for some function 
\begin_inset Formula $f$
\end_inset

.
 We do not make any 
\emph on
